task.summary: Abstracted function to check/change player image. Fixed Corridor Making Code to use SetSpace functionality - fixed bug that showed spaces as walls intermittently. Fixed Up/Down Stairs adding/detracting creatures from floors. Light Blue Potion works appropriately. Scroll of Recall appropriately recalls creature to level it was found on.
Hard cap to Level 100, stairs down will no longer spawn past that level. Room generation works, now trying to incorporate enemy and clutter generation. Minor optimizations to commonly used functions.
Coded, untested different movement type: towardtargetDirectionally. Coded, untested different movement limit: inLevel rather than inCamera. (all enemies with tag InLevel can move on that level).
coded different versions of creating stairs up and down in order to spawn them in separate rooms later in game lifecycle.
fixed bug where the stairs up wouldn't generate until level 2.
made win condition if player kills minotaur.
not sure what I did, everything is working. random movement fixed, directional movement works.
Trap void object work. Now every time the user mines rock, something is animated.
Sound is working: upon creation of a minotaur, the game roars at you.

Clutter now has an owner in preparation for shop creation. (If clutter.getOwner().getCellType == CellType.SHOPOWNER){items can only be picked up if the user has enough gold.} Objects creatures have are now set to be owned by them. Maps have better borders. Border thickness and border type can all be set in the creation stage. Optimized a few things in camera space: due to borders, now the camera can freely travel to places hithertoo unexplored without impeding the user's ability to see their stats. New sounds include walking, better dying sound, mining (succeed) and mining (fail). Player now screams when dead. Room creation drastically overhauled to accommodate upcoming shop, "treasure islands." Ring creation overhauled. Silver rings can now do the exact same things as gold rings and vice versa, but gold rings help the user more and their value has increased accordingly. New enchantment: featherFall, prevents fall damage. Void areas are pitfall traps. Falling into them will hurt you and load a new, lower level.

Reverting changes made to code by auto-code formatting to make it easier for me to read. Made Fog of War Bitmap Array - will be entirely made of black images. (spaces[5]) Bitmaps will have their opacity set by any lit light source radius. Update Enemies is no longer checking player.

Revamped Creatures: Creatures now have multiple DirectionTypes: -Still -Horizontal -Vertical -Horizontal and Vertical MovementTypes: -Random -An assortment of varying "Towards target" depending on creature intelligence. Handicaps: -For weaker creatures, they can only move so often. State: -Chase, Patrol, Wander, Gather, Rest. PatrolTypes: creatures can patrol in a line based on their movement type, or they can patrol between a list of points.
Lightsources are now set up to be lit no matter who has them. Potions can now be used against other creatures. Creature update code is now based on the entire dungeon to facilitate the move to making creatures chase you between levels. (Creatures chasing you between levels not yet thoroughly tested.) Rest times for creatures other than slimes have been drastically reduced. BUGFIX: creatures going down levels will now only generate the next level. Black potions now act like acid: they destroy an item. LIGHTING: The dungeon is dark now! the player has to keep moving to keep the lights going. Spawned items are now set to the same lighting as the point they are spawned on.
Creatures now spawn with patrols, handicaps, movementTypes, states, etc. Creatures now drop their lights if they have them. Mining: Shovels only spawn rocks and traps. (Rocks far more often than traps.) Pickaxes spawn rocks, diamonds, and traps. (Rocks and diamonds far more often than traps). Traps are now spawned more often. Breaking walls will no longer spawn diamonds at all. (Diamonds are made under pressure.) Maps now have borders! The borders can change thickness and type. (Walls, spaces, Impenetrable walls, void spaces, etc.) Healing is now nerfed. When you heal and you're at current health, your max health only increases if you've explored more.
SoundPool now let's multiple sounds play at once.
